//! FreeLang Self-Hosting VM
//!
//! A stack-based bytecode virtual machine for executing FreeLang programs.
//!
//! # Architecture
//!
//! The VM consists of several key components:
//!
//! - **VM**: Main execution engine with stack, heap, and registers
//! - **Memory**: 64KB memory management (stack, heap, globals)
//! - **Bytecode**: Bytecode loader and instruction definitions
//! - **GC**: Garbage collector for automatic memory management
//! - **Stdlib**: Standard library functions (println, array ops, etc.)
//!
//! # Example
//!
//! ```no_run
//! use freelang_vm::vm::VM;
//!
//! let bytecode = vec![
//!     0x01, 0x2A,  // PUSH 42
//!     0x60,        // PRINT
//!     0x61, 0x00,  // HALT 0
//! ];
//!
//! let mut vm = VM::new(&bytecode).unwrap();
//! vm.run().unwrap();  // Output: 42
//! ```

